&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/texts/feminist-organizational-theory-survey/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/texts/feminist-organizational-theory-survey/> ;
  schema:name "Feminist Organizational Theory: A Survey of How Governance Reproduces Gender Inequality" ;
  schema:description "Survey of feminist organizational theory from Acker, Calás and Smircich, Martin, Federici, and hooks—examining how governance structures are gendered, how formal neutrality reproduces power asymmetries, how invisible labor subsidizes governance, and why theory itself must center those marginalized by organizational structures." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-04-03" ;
  schema:dateModified "2026-04-03" ;
  schema:isPartOf &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/> ;
  emsenn:Introduces &lt;https://emsenn.net/tags/survey/> ;
  rdfs:seeAlso "Role, Office, Duty, Accountability, Work, Assignment, Delegation, Institution" ;
  emsenn:Sources "Acker, Joan. 'Hierarchies, Jobs, Bodies: A Theory of Gendered Organizations.' *Gender \u0026 Society*, vol. 4, no. 2, 1990, pp. 139-158." , "Calás, Marta B., and Linda Smircich. 'From the Woman's Point of View: Feminist Approaches to Organization Studies.' *Handbook of Organization Studies*, edited by Stewart R. Clegg et al., Sage, 1996." , "Martin, Patricia Yancey. 'Gendering and Evaluating Dynamics: Men, Masculinities, and Managements.' *Gender, Work \u0026 Organization*, vol. 8, no. 3, 2001." , "Martin, Patricia Yancey. '\"Said and Done\" Versus \"Saying and Doing\": Gendering Practices, Practicing Gender at Work.' *Gender \u0026 Society*, vol. 17, no. 3, 2003, pp. 342-366." , "Federici, Silvia. *Caliban and the Witch: Women, the Body and Primitive Accumulation*. Autonomedia, 2004." , "Federici, Silvia. *Revolution at Point Zero: Housework, Reproduction, and Feminist Struggle*. PM Press, 2012." , "hooks, bell. *Feminist Theory: From Margin to Center*. South End Press, 1984." ;
  emsenn:Surveys &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/> ;
